You can partion when the Windows Installer will ask you
where you want to install Windows
select your HD (usually the biggest in size as the other are just some
recovery partitions)

then click on format (this will erase all your data)
then click on 'Delete'

now you will get the unallocated space
Select it and click on 'New'
Now just specify the amount of space in megabytes to allocate for the installation
of Windows
Click 'Apply' and 'OK'

To create additional partitions Click on the remaining unallocated space (but you can do this manually
later when windows is installed)

then continue with the installation selecting the right HD just created 
